The `debounce` function is a utility function that prevents a function from being called too many times in a short period of time, often used to limit the rate of events such as window resizes or scrolls.

```javascript
function debounce(fn, delay) {
    let timeoutId;
    return function (...args) {
        if (timeoutId) {
            clearTimeout(timeoutId);
        }
        timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
            fn.apply(this, args);
        }, delay);
    };
}

// Example usage:
function handleResize() {
    console.log('Window resized');
}

const debouncedHandleResize = debounce(handleResize, 500);

window.addEventListener('resize', debouncedHandleResize);
```
